HEADWORD: Concitation
<hw>Con`ci*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>concitatio</ets>. See <er>Concite</er>.]</ety> <def>The act of
stirring up, exciting, or agitating.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>concitation</xex> of humors.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Sir T.
Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
